	<h2 class="title" id="title-ruby-development"><a href="#" title="Ruby on Rails System Development">Ruby on Rails System Development</a></h2>
    <p><strong>Ruby on Rails transformed the way we think about building web applications.</strong></p>

    <p>We use <a href="http://www.ruby-lang.org/">Ruby</a> because it's an exciting and compelling technology that doesn't hurt. It allows us to build professional and quality software fast, while being nimble to react to change.</p>

    <p>Technically, Ruby's flexible/expressive, dynamic, object oriented and message passing nature let's use think of solutions that model the real world of our clients domain.</p>

    <p>Like the characteristics of fine red wine, we use a blend of tools to complement our web development services, namely Rails and Sinatra.</p>

    <p>We use <a href="http://rubyonrails.org/">Rails</a> because its leverages the power of Ruby and brings it to the web. Rails conventions allow us to get on with the job of building immediate business value rather than having to satisfy the requirements of large frameworks and environments before writing a line of code.</p>

    <p>We use <a href="http://www.sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a> because its light design and compact mindset allows us to build focused web services rapidly.</p>
